The Trump administration has repealed a rule that was intended to punish oil and gas producers. This regulation, implemented under Barack Obama, would have added significant costs to fracking operations by imposing burdensome and duplicative red tape on energy producers operating on public lands. The editorial argues that sensible and innovative domestic energy development, including fracking, has led to an abundance of cheap and reliable fuel and an economic boom. The Trump administration's deregulation agenda has been highlighted as a significant accomplishment in his first year in office, with more than a dozen major rules imposed by Obama being wiped off the books.